==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Exasperation
<hw>Ex*as`per*a"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>exasperatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>exasp⟦eacute⟧ration</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of exasperating or the state of being
exasperated; irritation; keen or bitter anger.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Extorted from him by the <qex>exasperation</qex> of his
spirits.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Increase of violence or malignity; aggravation;
exacerbation.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Exasperation</xex> of the fits.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Sir H. Wotton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Exaspidean</ent>⟦br⟧
